wikipedia_page.main: Harry George Tate (18 July 1862 – 9 March 1949) was an English cricketer who played one first-class cricket match for Somerset in 1882. He may have played more, but his work on the railways took him away from Taunton weeks after his sole appearance. He played as a batsman, and became a mainstay of the Caversham Cricket Club for two decades once he'd moved to Reading.
